  The Pi is the ONLY controller. There is no manual fallback.
  The software kill switch (Ctrl+C) and DETECTION_TIMEOUT
  safety hover are your only safety mechanisms.
  Keep the drone tethered or over a soft surface during all
  early testing.

HOW THE PROGRAM FLOWS (big picture):
─────────────────────────────────────
  Thread 1 — MSPSender._loop()
      Runs non-stop at 50 Hz.
      Every 20ms it grabs the latest channel values and
      sends them to the flight controller over serial.
      This thread NEVER pauses for camera work — if it did,
      Betaflight would see a gap in RC packets and trigger
      failsafe (motors cut, drone drops).

  Thread 2 — perception_thread()
      Captures frames from the CSI camera.
      Runs YOLO (or HOG fallback) on each frame.
      Writes the detected bounding box into SharedState.
      Runs as fast as the detector allows (~5–30 FPS).

  Main thread — main()
      Reads the latest bounding box from SharedState.
      Calculates how far off-centre the person is.
      Feeds those errors into three PID controllers.
      Writes resulting RC channel values to MSPSender
      so Thread 1 can send them.
      Also draws the debug overlay on screen.
"""

